==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Popelote
<hw>Pop"e*lote</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A word variously
explained as ⟦ldquo⟧a little puppet,⟦rdquo⟧ ⟦ldquo⟧a little doll,⟦rdquo⟧
or ⟦ldquo⟧a young butterfly.⟦rdquo⟧ Cf. <er>Popet</er>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So gay a <qex>popelote</qex>, so sweet a wench.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Popery</ent>⟦br⟧
